<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="156" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,704,1343]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" box="[257,447,704,730]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[257,447,704,730]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">Rubus ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published twice by Heinrich Wilhelm Schott, first in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">Väterländische Blätter für die österreichische Kaiserstaat</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schott, H. W." box="[505,702,740,766]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" pagination="61 - 67" refId="ref6117" refString="Schott, H. W. (1818 a) Auszuge aus den Berichten und Briefe der auf befehl Sr. Majestat des Kaisers nach Brasilien abgeschickten osterreichisschen Naturforscher an den Direktor des k. k. Hof-Naturkabinette Herrn Karl von Schreibers als Referenten des wissenschaftlichen Anteiles der Expedition. Vaterlandische Blatter fur den ostterreichische Kaiserstat I, 4 - 6, 37 - 44, 61 - 67." type="journal article" year="1818">Schott 1818a: 42</bibRefCitation>
) and subsequently in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schott 1818 b: 821)" baseAuthorityName="Schott" baseAuthorityPageNumber="821" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[955,1235,740,766]" class="Anthozoa" family="Isididae" genus="Isis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[955,994,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">Isis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schott, H. W." box="[1011,1226,740,766]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" pagination="818 - 822" refId="ref6187" refString="Schott, H. W. (1818 b) Botanische Berichte von Schott in Europa. Isis oder Encyclopadische Zeitung 2 - 3: 818 - 822." type="journal article" year="1818">Schott 1818b: 821</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It was typified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, H. E." box="[136,291,776,803]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" refId="ref6853" refString="Weber, H. E. (1986 [' 1985 ']). Rubi Westfalici. Die Brombeerarten Westfalens und des Raumes Osnabruck (Rubus L., Subgenus Rubus). Westfalisches Museum fur Naturkunde, Munster, 452 pp." type="book" year="1986">Weber (1986)</bibRefCitation>
from a specimen preserved at W. There is no doubt about its identity, it is the discolour blackberry, i.e. a blackberry with abaxially white tomentose leaves, with strongly pruinose stems and small leaves, which is the most common species in South-West Europe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,704,1343]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">
As a diploid taxon it has a large variability in contrast to the apogamous taxa which 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1278,884,910]" form="the" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" rank="form">form the</taxonomicName>
bulk of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1381,1451,884,910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">Rubus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in Europe. Because earlier botanists were not aware of this difference they dealt with the variations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the same way as with the apogamous taxa. This resulted in a large number of related taxa, sometimes ordered as infraspecific taxa. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sudre, H." box="[462,599,992,1018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" refId="ref6303" refString="Sudre, H. (1908 - 1913) Rubi Europae, Lhomme, Paris, 305 + ccxv pp." type="book" year="1908">Sudre (1908</bibRefCitation>
–1913) recognized 8 subspecies, 20 microgenera (an unfortunate word for an infraspecific rank!) and 94 varieties. Next to these many synonyms are listed. Most of these do not have real taxonomic value. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E." box="[209,608,1064,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" pagination="311 - 322" refId="ref5806" refString="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E. (1996) Taxonomy and nomenclature of Rubus ulmifolius and Rubus sanctus (Rosaceae). Edinburgh Journal of Botany 33: 311 - 322. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428600003759" type="journal article" year="1996">Monasterio-Huelin &amp; Weber (1996)</bibRefCitation>
reduced the number of infraspecific taxa to 4 varieties. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" box="[1221,1408,1064,1090]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[1221,1408,1064,1090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">Rubus ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also many hybrids, often with unknown other parents.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="156" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,704,1343]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">
Before 
<bibRefCitation author="Focke, W. O." box="[272,422,1136,1162]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" refId="ref5152" refString="Focke, W. O. (1877) Synopsis ruborum Germaniae: Die deutschen Brombeerarten ausfuhrlich beschrieben und erlautert. C. Ed. Mullers's Verlagsbuchhandlung, Bremen, 434 pp." type="book" year="1877">Focke (1877)</bibRefCitation>
recuperated the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" box="[674,817,1136,1162]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[674,817,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most authors used other, later names for the species, e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Weihe &amp; Nees (1824: 46)" authorityName="Weihe &amp; Nees" authorityPageNumber="46" authorityYear="1824" box="[136,555,1172,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis box="[136,260,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">R. discolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weihe, K. E. A. &amp; Nees von Esenbeck, C. G. D." box="[266,555,1172,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" pagination="29 - 46" refId="ref6951" refString="Weihe, K. E. A. &amp; Nees von Esenbeck, C. G. D. (1824) Rubi Germanici. Die deutsche Brombeerstrauche, Fasciculus III et IV. Schonian'sche Buchhandlung, Elberfeld, pp. 29 - 46." type="book chapter" year="1824">Weihe &amp; Nees (1824: 46)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Mercier (1861: 279)" authorityName="Mercier" authorityPageNumber="279" authorityYear="1861" box="[593,979,1172,1198]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rusticanus">
<emphasis box="[593,742,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">R. rusticanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mercier, E." box="[749,979,1172,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156" refId="ref5719" refString="Mercier, E. (1861) Monographie des especes du genre Rubus des environs de Geneve. In: Reuter, G. F. (Ed.) Catalogue des Plantes Vasculaires qui croissent naturellement aux environs de Geneve, ed. 2. Kesemann, Geneve, 295 pp." type="book" year="1861">Mercier (1861: 279)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but since Focke’s publication is has been in common use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="156" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,704,1343]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">
There is no doubt about the identity of the 
<typeStatus box="[675,727,1245,1271]" pageId="1" pageNumber="156">type</typeStatus>
. It consists of both an inflorescence and a piece of a primocane. On the label is written ‘In sepibus maritimis Hispaniae’ which corresponds well with the locality in the protologue: ‘in montosis Gibraltariae’, or at least does not contradict it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
